---
[severity:It's more difficult to complete my work]
I have a Blazor Wasm app. There is a class FooData with several properties.

public class FooData
    {
        public int Foo1 { get; set; } = -999;
        public double Foo2 { get; set; } = -999d;
        ...
    }
And there is a class BarUnits

public class BarUnits : ComponentBase
    {
        public IEnumerable<FooData> IFooDataS { get; set; }

protected override Task OnInitializedAsync()
        {
            LoadFooData();
            return base. OnInitializedAsync();
        }

private void LoadFooData()
        {
            var h1 = new FooData { Foo1 = 1, Foo2 = 2d, ...};
            var h2 = new FooData { Foo1 = 3, Foo2 = 4d, ...};
            ...

IFooDataS = new List<FooData> { h1, h2, ... h1400};
        }
    }

FooData contains about 100 properties and `LoadFooData` creates 1400 `new FooData`. During development, this is not a problem, but a publish build with enabled AOT compilation fails.

> C:\Program Files\dotnet\packs\Microsoft.NET.Runtime.WebAssembly.Sdk\6.0.16\Sdk\WasmApp.Native.targets(511,5): Error : Precompiling failed for C:\[...] \obj\Release\net6.0\linked\<appName>.dll.

I tried the following:

1. I reduced `IFooDataS = new List<FooData> { h1, h2, ... h1400};` to `IFooDataS = new List<FooData> { h1, h2, ... h670};` but kept the unused `var h671 = ` to `var h1400 = `. This resulted in a working publish build.
 2. With `IFooDataS = new List<FooData> { h1, h2, ... h671};` (one more item) the publish build does not work.
 3. But when I now comment out the unused items `var h1390 = ` to `var h1400 = ` the publish build works.
 4. Splitting and concatenating does not work: `IFooDataS = IFoo1.Concat(IFoo2). Concat(IFoo2);` results in a publish build error.

I asked for a solution on [Stack overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/76587272/how-can-i-avoid-aot-build-error-during-publish-build-in-blazor-wasm) and received a proposal for a workaround.
  5. I split `LoadFooData()` into `LoadFoo1()`, `LoadFoo2()`, `LoadFoo3()` and changed `LoadFooData()` to

```
    private void LoadFooData()
    {
        IHexDataS = IFoo1.Concat(IFoo2). Concat(IFoo3);
    }
```
With this workaround, the publish build works.

